Introduction¶

Our Purpose is to Data analysis on a sample Dataset to try to understand the possible reasons for the patients from the sample not to attend their appointments, then try to allocate resources to solve those issues to give patients better health care.

Data Wrangling¶

Data Description¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.
- ScheduledDay tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.
- Neighborhood indicates thelocation of the hospital.
- Scholarship indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Famlia.
- Be careful about the encoding of the last column: it says No if the patient showed up to their appointment, and Yes if they did not show up.
- Category Categorize according to gender and age (Child, Man, Women,Elderly People).

Categorize people into four categories according to Age & Gender (child, Woman, Man, elderly) to ease some studies.¶

Assumption: With 'child' and 'Elderly People' not classified in the data, I'll need to assume a cutoff point. Therefore, I'll be using today's standard of under 18 as those to be considered as a child and over 60 considered as elderly people.

In [263]:
# Split Patients into four categories according to Gender & Age to ease the study.
df.loc[((df['Gender'] == 'F') &(df['Age'] >= 18)),'Category'] = 'Woman'
df.loc[((df['Gender'] == 'M') & (df['Age'] >= 18)),'Category'] = 'Man'
df.loc[(df['Age'] < 18),'Category'] = 'Child'
df.loc[(df['Age'] > 60),'Category'] = 'Elderly'

def plotting(df,char_1,char_2,plot_kind,fig_size):
    '''
    This function is used to plot a graph to describe the Numbers of patients with certain charactaristic(s) who attended or didn't attend there appointments.
    Arrguments:
    df: DataFrame which includes the charactaristics we want to study its influence on attending, with a coloumn that shows if the patients attend or not.
    char_1: Coloumn name that shows if the patients attend or not with values that must be like follows ('No' for attending the appointment & 'Yes' for skipping the appointment).
    char_2: The Charactaristic we want to study its influence on showing or not showing for appointment
    plot_kind: Either Histogram or Bar(Horizontal or Vertical) entries can be as follows('hist', 'bar', 'barh') 
    fig_size: list of length and width of the desired graph (ex. [10,10])
    '''
    #Assign Names to patients who showed and doesn't showed to make the recalling and comparison easier.
    Show = df[char_1] == 'No'
    No_Show = df[char_1] == 'Yes' 
    char_show = df[char_2][Show]
    char_no_show = df[char_2][No_Show]
    if plot_kind == 'hist':
        plt.figure(figsize= fig_size)
        plt.hist(char_show,alpha=0.5,label='Showed for appointment',color='Blue',edgecolor='black')
        plt.hist(char_no_show,alpha=0.5,label='Did not show for appointment',color='Red',edgecolor='black')
        plt.legend()
        plt.title('Showing & No-Showing for the appointments according to {}'.format(char_2))
        plt.xlabel('{}'.format(char_2))
        plt.ylabel('Patients Number');
    elif plot_kind == 'bar'or 'barh':
        plt.figure(figsize= fig_size)
        char_show.value_counts().plot(kind = 'bar',label='Showed for appointment',color='Blue',alpha = 0.75)
        char_no_show.value_counts().plot(kind = 'bar',label='Did not show for appointment',color='Red',alpha = 0.75)
        plt.legend()
        plt.title('Showing & No-Showing for the appointments according to {}'.format(char_2))
        plt.xlabel('{}'.format(char_2))
        plt.ylabel('Patients Number');
        
def print_values(df,char_1,char_2):
    '''
    This function is used to print numbers to describe  of patients with certain charactaristic(s) who attended or didn't attend there appointments
    df: DataFrame which includes the charactaristics we want to study its influence on attending, with a coloumn that shows if the patients attend or not.
    char_1: Coloumn name that shows if the patients attend or not with values that must be like follows ('No' for attending the appointment & 'Yes' for skipping the appointment).
    char_2: The Charactaristic we want to study its influence on showing or not showing for appointment
    '''
    Show = df[char_1] == 'No'
    No_Show = df[char_1] == 'Yes'
    if char_2 == 'Gender':
        female_s =  len(df[((df[char_2] == 'F') &(df[char_1] == 'No'))])
        female_ns = len(df[((df[char_2] == 'F') &(df[char_1] == 'Yes'))])
        male_s =  len(df[((df[char_2] == 'M') &(df[char_1] == 'No'))])
        male_ns = len(df[((df[char_2] == 'M') &(df[char_1] == 'Yes'))])
        print ("The Number of female patients who showed for the appointments is {} patients.".format(female_s))
        print ("The Number of female patients who didn't show for the appointments is {} patients.".format(female_ns))
        print ("The Number of Male patients who showed for the appointments is {} patients.".format(male_s))
        print ("The Number of Male patients who didn't show for the appointments is {} patients.".format(male_ns))
    else:
            char_s = len(df[((df[char_2] == 1) &(df[char_1] == 'No'))])
            char_ns = len(df[((df[char_2] == 1) &(df[char_1] == 'Yes'))])
            nchar_s = len(df[((df[char_2] == 0) &(df[char_1] == 'No'))])
            nchar_ns = len(df[((df[char_2] == 0) &(df[char_1] == 'Yes'))])
            print('The Number of patients who have {} and showed for the appointments is {} patients.'.format(char_2,char_s))
            print("The Number of patients who have {} and didn't show for the appointments is {} patients.".format(char_2,char_ns))
            print("The Number of patients who didn't have {} and showed for the appointments is {} patients.".format(char_2,nchar_s))
            print("The Number of patients who didn't have {} and didn't show for the appointments is {} patients.".format(char_2,nchar_s))

Conclusions¶

Analysis with respecting to age only have no major previously unknown significance that age influence attending the appointments but we can conclude that Patients with age ranges between 0 - 15 years old are most likely to attend there appointments more than any other age range follwed by people with age range 45, while the patients who passes 60 most likely to skip the appointments from which we can tell that they find difficulties going to clinics or hospitals, so we can recommend that they should intiate a program to give the elderly patients health care in their homes without going to hospitals or clinics, while when analyzing with respect to Gender only and the anlayzing after categorizing the sample to Age-Gender Categorizes, we can mainly conclude that Female adults ( Women with age above 18 ) are more cautious about their health than men.

While for other points it was Shocking that Receving an SMS as a reminder to the patients about their appointments doesn't affect their attendance, which takes as to maybe consider to advance to next level to make sure that the patient remember his/here appointment maybe by making calls to them directlty to ensure that the reminder is succesfully received by the patient but financial wise it will be a heavy load on the hospitals.

While Analyzing with respect to neighbourhood that patients live at led us to a conclusion that this is a major point that affect attendance of patients as there is a major variation between the numbers of attending patients from different neighbourhoods but we must have data about those neighbourhoods to know the reasons of this variation and answer some questions about the distance of each neighbourhood to the clinics, if transportation is available or not.

Limitations:

  • Lack of Information about Neighbourhoods which prevented deep analysis for the attendance with respect to the information of various neighbourhoods.
  • There is no charactaristics equity in the samples, For example, The Number of Handicapped patients samples is very small with respect to the normal patients which can bias the judgement and conclusions if not noticed, These also found in many of other charactaristics.
